  node [
    id 0
    label "0"
    text "Visual perception is one of the most heavily studied areas in cognitive neuroscience, and for good reason&#8212;vision dominates our sensory experience"
  ]
  node [
    id 1
    label "1"
    text " My research focuses on the neural coding of mid-level visual features&#8212;things like shape contours, surface texture, and spatial frequency&#8212;and how those features contribute to object recognition"
  ]
  node [
    id 2
    label "2"
    text " We use a mix of fMRI, EEG, and psychophysical tasks to map out the stages of the visual hierarchy, from V1 all the way up to the inferotemporal cortex"
  ]
  node [
    id 3
    label "3"
    text " What&#8217;s fascinating is how early processing is so fast and feedforward, but later stages involve feedback loops, attention modulation, and even top-down expectation"
  ]
  node [
    id 4
    label "4"
    text " There&#8217;s also a growing interest in how perception isn&#8217;t just passive"
  ]
  node [
    id 5
    label "5"
    text " We now think of it as inference&#8212;where the brain makes predictions about the world and updates based on sensory input"
  ]
  node [
    id 6
    label "6"
    text " That&#8217;s why illusions are so interesting: they reveal the assumptions the system is making"
  ]
  node [
    id 7
    label "7"
    text " We&#8217;ve started integrating machine vision comparisons as well&#8212;like testing how convolutional neural networks respond to the same distorted or occluded images we give to human participants"
  ]
  node [
    id 8
    label "8"
    text " The parallels are informative, but also highlight key differences in generalization and robustness"
  ]
  node [
    id 9
    label "9"
    text " Understanding vision isn&#8217;t just about biology&#8212;it helps in everything from building better prosthetics to designing more readable user interfaces"
  ]
  node [
    id 10
    label "10"
    text " It&#8217;s one of the rare domains where theory and application constantly feed into each other"
  ]
  node [
    id 11
    label "11"
    text " We're also studying how attention acts as a filter"
  ]
  node [
    id 12
    label "12"
    text " It's not just about what reaches your eyes, but what your brain decides to process further"
  ]
  node [
    id 13
    label "13"
    text " Selective attention can modulate neural responses as early as V2 and V4 in the visual stream"
  ]
  node [
    id 14
    label "14"
    text " Some of the most exciting work is happening at the intersection of perception and action&#8212;how vision guides motor planning"
  ]
  node [
    id 15
    label "15"
    text " This has implications for robotics and prosthetics, where feedback loops are essential"
  ]
  node [
    id 16
    label "16"
    text " And increasingly, we&#8217;re interested in individual differences"
  ]
  node [
    id 17
    label "17"
    text " Why do some people notice fine-grained visual detail while others miss it? Is it training, genetics, or something else entirely? There&#8217;s still so much to uncover"
  ]
